## 🐛 Bug Report!
Except for print_title, DefinedName and localSheetId are lost.
Lib version: exceljs@4.2.1

## Steps To Reproduce

 1. make EXCEL-book by MS-EXCEL that's Named ranges with the same name on different pages.
 2. Load the XLSX-Book-file in exceljs and write it. 
　　(Nothing changes XLSX-object, as shown in the javascript-code at the bellow)
 3.  Compare the contents of the /xl/workbook.xml in the excel-book zip directory  to before load and after write.
   Please see the attached figure.
   Except for print_title, DefinedName and localSheetId are lost. 

```javascript code
var workBook1 = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
workBook1.xlsx.load(fileData1)
 .then(workBook2 => {
    console.log("at loaded definedName id lost:", workBook2)
    return  workBook2.xlsx.writeBuffer()
                 .then(wbout1 => {
                      saveAs(new Blob([wbout1], { type: "application/octet-stream" }), newBookName);
                  });
                });
           })
```

 * Compared the contents:
![exceljs-lost-definedNames-bug3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/64691446/133082709-29799867-f021-4b0f-9d12-17807de55326.png)

## The expected behaviour:

- Expect the DefinedName and localSheetId not to be lost. 
-  Similar to MS-excel, which allows exceljs-API to define named ranges with the same name on different pages. 
-  I also hope that the following issues will be resolved.
    https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/issues/1497
    https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/issues/393

## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):
　None, for long times.
